PTM: First processed by the removal of 4 Arg residues by furin- type protease, forming two chains, alpha and gamma/beta precursor, linked by a disulfide bond. Probably, the cobrin cleaves the C3a- like domain and then the C3d-like domain, generating the mature cobra venom factor (CVF). This mature CVF is composed of three chains: alpha, gamma and beta. These chains are linked by a disulfide bond between the alpha and gamma chains and another one between the gamma and beta chains.
